Note: ============================================================================
Note: Registry record layout (48 bytes per record, fixed)
Note: ============================================================================
Note: Field layout (offsets within a record block):
Note:   0    iso_alpha_ptr        (pointer to 3-4 char ASCII string)
Note:   8    iso_numeric          (int64, -1 for non-ISO entries)
Note:   16   display_name_ptr     (pointer to UTF-8 display name)
Note:   24   symbol_ptr           (pointer to UTF-8 symbol)
Note:   32   decimal_exponent     (int64, minor-unit exponent)
Note:   40   classification       (int64, CURRENCY_CLASS_*)
Note: ============================================================================

Constant CURRENCY_RECORD_SIZE as Integer is 48
Constant CURRENCY_FIELD_ALPHA as Integer is 0
Constant CURRENCY_FIELD_NUMERIC as Integer is 8
Constant CURRENCY_FIELD_NAME as Integer is 16
Constant CURRENCY_FIELD_SYMBOL as Integer is 24
Constant CURRENCY_FIELD_EXPONENT as Integer is 32
Constant CURRENCY_FIELD_CLASS as Integer is 40

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Registry lifecycle - caller-owned base pointer
Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pattern: the application invokes currency_registry_initialize_once at
Note: process start and retains the returned base pointer. Lookup procs take
Note: the base as their first parameter. This avoids the need for module
Note: statics and gives the application explicit ownership of the registry
Note: lifetime. Treasury and ledger applications use this exact pattern: one
Note: registry per node, initialized at boot, destroyed at shutdown.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "currency_registry_initialize_once" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    One-time initialization: allocates a fresh table, populates every
    registered currency, and returns the base pointer. Caller is
    expected to hold the returned base and pass it to lookup procs.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Allocate (MAX_ID + 1) * RECORD_SIZE bytes via Layout.allocate (zeroed),
    invoke currency_register_all to populate slots 1..MAX_ID, return base.
    Slot 0 is reserved as INVALID and remains zero.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Linear in number of registered currencies. ~167 records * ~6 fields
    each = ~1000 simple stores. Sub-microsecond.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Allocates one heap block. Returns 0 on allocation failure.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let table_size be CURRENCY_MAX_ID multiplied by CURRENCY_RECORD_SIZE
    Set table_size to table_size plus CURRENCY_RECORD_SIZE
    Let base be Layout.allocate(table_size)
    If base is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    currency_register_all(base)
    Return base
End Process

Process called "currency_registry_destroy" takes base as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Releases the registry table. Pairs with currency_registry_initialize_once.
    String literals embedded in slots are static and are not freed.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single Layout.deallocate call.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Safe on null base.
    @End Security_Scope

    If base is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Layout.deallocate(base)
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Slot accessor (computes record address for a given currency_id)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "currency_slot_address" takes base as Integer, currency_id as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Computes the byte address of the record for currency_id within the
    table. Returns 0 for invalid IDs (out of range).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    address = base + currency_id * CURRENCY_RECORD_SIZE
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single multiply-add.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Range-checks against CURRENCY_MAX_ID.
    @End Security_Scope

    If base is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If currency_id is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If currency_id is greater than CURRENCY_MAX_ID:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let offset be currency_id multiplied by CURRENCY_RECORD_SIZE
    Return base plus offset
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Slot population helper - writes a single record into the table.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "currency_set_slot" takes base as Integer, currency_id as Integer, iso_alpha as Integer, iso_numeric as Integer, display_name as Integer, symbol as Integer, decimal_exponent as Integer, classification as Integer returns Integer:
    Let slot be currency_slot_address(base, currency_id)
    If slot is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    MemoryCore.memory_set_int64(slot, CURRENCY_FIELD_ALPHA, iso_alpha)
    MemoryCore.memory_set_int64(slot, CURRENCY_FIELD_NUMERIC, iso_numeric)
    MemoryCore.memory_set_int64(slot, CURRENCY_FIELD_NAME, display_name)
    MemoryCore.memory_set_int64(slot, CURRENCY_FIELD_SYMBOL, symbol)
    MemoryCore.memory_set_int64(slot, CURRENCY_FIELD_EXPONENT, decimal_exponent)
    MemoryCore.memory_set_int64(slot, CURRENCY_FIELD_CLASS, classification)
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Field accessors - public API
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "currency_get_iso_alpha" takes base as Integer, currency_id as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the ISO 4217 alpha code (3-4 char ASCII string pointer) for
    the given currency. Returns 0 for invalid currency_id.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Slot field load.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure read. Range-checked.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let slot be currency_slot_address(base, currency_id)
    If slot is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return MemoryCore.memory_get_int64(slot, CURRENCY_FIELD_ALPHA)
End Process

Process called "currency_get_iso_numeric" takes base as Integer, currency_id as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the ISO 4217 numeric code (per ISO 4217:2015). Returns -1 for
    non-ISO entries (crypto, sovereign, commodity) and 0 for invalid id.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Slot field load.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure read.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let slot be currency_slot_address(base, currency_id)
    If slot is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return MemoryCore.memory_get_int64(slot, CURRENCY_FIELD_NUMERIC)
End Process

Process called "currency_get_display_name" takes base as Integer, currency_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Let slot be currency_slot_address(base, currency_id)
    If slot is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return MemoryCore.memory_get_int64(slot, CURRENCY_FIELD_NAME)
End Process

Process called "currency_get_symbol" takes base as Integer, currency_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Let slot be currency_slot_address(base, currency_id)
    If slot is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return MemoryCore.memory_get_int64(slot, CURRENCY_FIELD_SYMBOL)
End Process

Process called "currency_get_decimal_exponent" takes base as Integer, currency_id as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the minor-unit decimal exponent. USD/EUR/most fiat = 2,
    JPY/KRW/no-cent fiat = 0, BHD/KWD/JOD/OMR = 3, BTC = 8, ETH = 18,
    SC = 18 (wei-style smart-contract precision). The amount of a Money
    value is stored as: major_value * 10^exponent (integer minor units).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Slot field load.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure read.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let slot be currency_slot_address(base, currency_id)
    If slot is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return MemoryCore.memory_get_int64(slot, CURRENCY_FIELD_EXPONENT)
End Process

Process called "currency_get_classification" takes base as Integer, currency_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Let slot be currency_slot_address(base, currency_id)
    If slot is equal to 0:
        Return CURRENCY_CLASS_INVALID
    End If
    Return MemoryCore.memory_get_int64(slot, CURRENCY_FIELD_CLASS)
End Process

Process called "currency_is_fiat" takes base as Integer, currency_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be currency_get_classification(base, currency_id)
    If c is equal to CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "currency_is_crypto" takes base as Integer, currency_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be currency_get_classification(base, currency_id)
    If c is equal to CURRENCY_CLASS_CRYPTO:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "currency_is_sovereign" takes base as Integer, currency_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be currency_get_classification(base, currency_id)
    If c is equal to CURRENCY_CLASS_SOVEREIGN:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "currency_is_commodity" takes base as Integer, currency_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be currency_get_classification(base, currency_id)
    If c is equal to CURRENCY_CLASS_COMMODITY:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "currency_is_valid" takes base as Integer, currency_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be currency_get_classification(base, currency_id)
    If c is equal to CURRENCY_CLASS_INVALID:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Lookup by alpha code (linear scan; small fixed table, branch-prediction
Note: friendly). High-frequency code paths cache the resolved id.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "currency_from_iso_code" takes base as Integer, alpha_code as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Resolves an ISO 4217 alpha code (e.g. "USD") to a currency_id. Linear
    scan over all registered entries. Returns CURRENCY_ID_INVALID for
    unknown codes.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    For each id from 1 to CURRENCY_MAX_ID, compare slot iso_alpha to the
    input via StringCore.string_equals. First match wins. Codes are stored
    in uppercase ASCII; callers may pre-normalize if required.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(N) where N=167. ~30ns per slot on contemporary hardware. Acceptable
    for boot-time parsing; cache the resolved id for hot paths.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Read-only scan. Caller must supply a NUL-terminated string pointer.
    Null input returns CURRENCY_ID_INVALID.
    @End Security_Scope

    If base is equal to 0:
        Return CURRENCY_ID_INVALID
    End If
    If alpha_code is equal to 0:
        Return CURRENCY_ID_INVALID
    End If
    Let id be 1
    While id is less than or equal to CURRENCY_MAX_ID:
        Let slot_alpha be currency_get_iso_alpha(base, id)
        If slot_alpha is not equal to 0:
            If StringCore.string_equals(slot_alpha, alpha_code) is equal to 1:
                Return id
            End If
        End If
        Set id to id plus 1
    End While
    Return CURRENCY_ID_INVALID
End Process

Process called "currency_from_numeric_code" takes base as Integer, numeric_code as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Resolves an ISO 4217 numeric code (e.g. 840 for USD) to a currency_id.
    Numeric codes are unique per ISO 4217:2015 and stable across revisions.
    Returns CURRENCY_ID_INVALID for unknown or non-ISO codes.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Linear scan; first match wins. Codes < 1 are rejected up front.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(N) where N=167.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Read-only.
    @End Security_Scope

    If base is equal to 0:
        Return CURRENCY_ID_INVALID
    End If
    If numeric_code is less than 1:
        Return CURRENCY_ID_INVALID
    End If
    Let id be 1
    While id is less than or equal to CURRENCY_MAX_ID:
        Let slot_numeric be currency_get_iso_numeric(base, id)
        If slot_numeric is equal to numeric_code:
            Return id
        End If
        Set id to id plus 1
    End While
    Return CURRENCY_ID_INVALID
End Process

Process called "currency_equals" takes currency_a as Integer, currency_b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Currency equality by id. Two currencies are equal iff they share a
    registry slot. This is the core safety predicate for money arithmetic:
    money_add rejects when currency_equals returns 0.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Integer equality.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single comparison.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope

    If currency_a is equal to currency_b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Populate the registry. Every currency in the catalogue is registered
Note: with its ISO alpha, ISO numeric (-1 for non-ISO), display name, symbol,
Note: decimal exponent, and classification.
Note: ============================================================================
Note: ISO numeric codes are per ISO 4217:2015. Exponents reflect the minor
Note: unit conventions from the ISO 4217 maintenance list (SIX Financial
Note: Information). Crypto exponents follow the canonical wei/satoshi values.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "currency_register_all" takes base as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Fiat - top reserve currencies
    currency_set_slot(base, CURRENCY_USD, "USD", 840, "United States dollar", "$", 2, CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT)
    currency_set_slot(base, CURRENCY_EUR, "EUR", 978, "Euro", "EUR", 2, CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT)
    currency_set_slot(base, CURRENCY_GBP, "GBP", 826, "Pound sterling", "GBP", 2, CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT)
    currency_set_slot(base, CURRENCY_JPY, "JPY", 392, "Japanese yen", "JPY", 0, CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT)
    currency_set_slot(base, CURRENCY_CNY, "CNY", 156, "Chinese yuan renminbi", "CNY", 2, CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT)
    currency_set_slot(base, CURRENCY_CHF, "CHF", 756, "Swiss franc", "CHF", 2, CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT)
    currency_set_slot(base, CURRENCY_AUD, "AUD", 36, "Australian dollar", "A$", 2, CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT)
    currency_set_slot(base, CURRENCY_CAD, "CAD", 124, "Canadian dollar", "C$", 2, CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT)
    currency_set_slot(base, CURRENCY_NZD, "NZD", 554, "New Zealand dollar", "NZ$", 2, CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT)
    currency_set_slot(base, CURRENCY_SGD, "SGD", 702, "Singapore dollar", "S$", 2, CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT)

    Note: Fiat - Asia
    currency_set_slot(base, CURRENCY_HKD, "HKD", 344, "Hong Kong dollar", "HK$", 2, CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT)
    currency_set_slot(base, CURRENCY_KRW, "KRW", 410, "South Korean won", "KRW", 0, CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT)
    currency_set_slot(base, CURRENCY_INR, "INR", 356, "Indian rupee", "INR", 2, CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT)
    currency_set_slot(base, CURRENCY_TWD, "TWD", 901, "New Taiwan dollar", "NT$", 2, CURRENCY_CLASS_FIAT)
